Rising star Tina Dlathu will make her debut on 1Magic’s popular telenovela The River tonight. Tina is the sister of lead actress Sindi Dlathu, who plays the villain role of Lindiwe Dikana. Tina will portray the role of Khwezi Hlophe, who is the daughter of the Hlophe family.  This season the telenovela has introduced several new faces including former Imbewu: The Seed actress Brenda Mhlongo, former Isibaya actor Bheki Mkhwane, Unathi Mkhize, and Vuyo Biyela, who plays Khwezi’s brother. Khwezi is the smartest and most obedient of all the children. She represents a South African born-free who grew up in a traditional Zulu home with a strict father.  Also Read: Mhlongo throttles producer on set For the latest entertainment news from Sunday World, click here. Or read the latest from Shwashwi here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here